{"lemma":"شَوْطٌ","slug":"شَوْطٌ","root":"ش.#.ط","root_slug":"ش-_-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-_-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n23324"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%92%D8%B7%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"stage, phase","examples":[{"text":"شَوْطُ ٱلْحَيَاةِ","english":"a stage of life"},{"text":"قَطَعَ شَوْطًا كَبِيرًا","english":"to make great progress"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"set, half, round","examples":[{"text":"الشَّوْطُ ٱلْأَوَّلُ","english":"first half"},{"text":"الشَّوْطُ ٱلثَّانِيُ","english":"second half"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a circuit around the Kaaba during the tawaf","examples":[{"text":"أَشْوَاطُ ٱلطَّوَافِ","english":"circuits of the Kaaba"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʃawtˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n23324","headword_ar":"شَوْطٌ","root":"$wT","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A heat; a single run,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a run at once, to a goal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"limit;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K;) syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TalaqN","text_ar":"طَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$owaATN","text_ar":"اَشْوَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Mgh, Msb, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA $awoTFA","text_ar":"عَدَا شَوْطًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ran a heat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAfa","text_ar":"طَافَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAlbayoti saboEapa A^a$owaATK","text_ar":"بَالبَيْتِ سَبْعَةَ اَشْوَاطٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He performed seven circuits round the House"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of God, i. e. the Kaabeh]: (S, TA:) from the [Black] Stone to the [Black] Stone [again] is one"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awoT","text_ar":"شَوْط"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb, TA:) but some of the lawyers disapprove of this application of the term"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$wAT","text_ar":"اشواط"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IF, K, TA.) ―         -b2-  [It is also, app., an inf. n. used as an epithet: for one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='a $awoTN","text_ar":"جَا=ءَ شَوْطٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina Alxayoli","text_ar":"مِنَ الخَيْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sananN","text_ar":"سَنَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the latter part of the paragraph.] It is sometimes used in relation to the wind: so says Lth: and he cites the following as an instance in which the wind is meant:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wanaAziHK muEotakiri AlA^a$owaATi"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And a wind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"many a wind, exhausting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drying up, the waters, the blasts thereof bringing dust"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  And it is also [used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bout"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of shooting arrows. (T and M in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r$q","text_ar":"رشق"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"space of ground over which a horse runs; such as a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mayodaAn","text_ar":"مَيْدَان"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is [said by some to be] the primary signification; [but the primary signification is said by others to be the first given above; (see Har p. 574;)] and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta$owiyTapN","text_ar":"تَشْوِيطَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b5-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A scope; an object to be reached,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"accomplished;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"gaAyapN","text_ar":"غَايَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": whence the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~awoTu","text_ar":"الشَّوْطُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTiynN","text_ar":"بَطِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The scope is remote:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 574:) a prov., relating to the long extent of hope. (TA.) ―         -b6-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place between two elevated tracts of ground, through which water and men pass, as though it were a road, extending as far as the voice of a caller can be heard, then ending,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of such depth that it will conceal the camel and his rider, found only in plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft, ground, and producing good herbage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, O:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iyaATN","text_ar":"شِيَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (ISh, O, K;) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iwaATN","text_ar":"شِوَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (ISh, O.) Z writes it with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"s","text_ar":"س"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA. See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawoTN","text_ar":"سَوْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awoTu baraAHK","text_ar":"شَوْطُ بَرَاحٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu A=waY","text_ar":"اِبْنُ ا=وَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The jackal"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (IDrd, S, Z, O, L, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"some other beast."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awoTu","text_ar":"شَوْطُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baATilK","text_ar":"بَاطِلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawoTu baATilK","text_ar":"سَوْطُ بَاطِلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"swT","text_ar":"سوط"},{"kind":"text","text":": accord. to IDrd, it is not of established authority. (O.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","TA","ISh","O","K","IDrd","Z","L"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}